Skin of snout, between eyes, and sides of head, shagreened to granular; anterior and posterior parts of back, and upper and lower parts of flank, granular (
Fig. 3D
); dorsal surfaces of forelimb, thigh, tibia and tarsus, shagreened to sparsely granular; throat, chest, abdomen, and ventral surfaces of limbs, shagreened (
Fig. 3D
).

Notes on previous reports. This species was previously misidentified as
Uperodon triangularis
from Ponmudi hills (
Inger et al. 1984
) and Thiruvananthapuram district (Andrew et al . 2005) of Kerala state. The report of
U. anamalaiensis
from Munnar in Kerala (
Harpalani et al . 2015
) most likely refers to
U. montanus
(see Supplementary Table S1 for list of localities and references thereto).
